37
00:03:01,780 --> 00:03:07,500
So how does coffee impact the body?

38
00:03:07,500 --> 00:03:13,340
When caffeine enters your digestive system it's absorbed by the intestine into the bloodstream.

39
00:03:13,340 --> 00:03:18,419
But the effects only start when caffeine hits the nervous system.

40
00:03:18,419 --> 00:03:22,539
This happens because caffeine has a chemical structure very similar to that of a substance

41
00:03:22,539 --> 00:03:28,819
produced by our own body, a denocene.

42
00:03:28,819 --> 00:03:37,460
Caffeine binds to the body's adenosine receptors, which can be found on the surface of nerve cells.

43
00:03:37,460 --> 00:03:40,420
It's like a key opening a lock.

44
00:03:40,420 --> 00:03:44,420
A denocene is known to slow down the sympathetic nervous system.

45
00:03:44,420 --> 00:03:51,260
It reduces your heart rate and generates a state of drowsiness and relaxation.

46
00:03:51,260 --> 00:03:55,900
By blocking these receptors caffeine generates the opposite effect.

47
00:03:55,900 --> 00:04:01,420
Your blood pressure for example may increase slightly, especially if you are not used to

48
00:04:01,420 --> 00:04:03,460
