49
00:04:03,460 --> 00:04:05,820
The same goes for brain activity.

50
00:04:05,820 --> 00:04:11,260
Caffeine stimulates the brain, suppresses hunger and helps you stay in a state of alertness

51
00:04:11,260 --> 00:04:15,020
so you can concentrate for longer.

52
00:04:15,020 --> 00:04:20,300
Caffeine can have a positive impact on your mood, inhibit feelings of fatigue and can

53
00:04:20,300 --> 00:04:22,500
improve physical performance.

54
00:04:22,500 --> 00:04:25,060
So many athletes use it as a supplement.

55
00:04:25,060 --> 00:04:28,939
These effects can last between 15 minutes and two hours.

56
00:04:28,939 --> 00:04:32,620
The body removes caffeine five to ten hours after consuming it.

57
00:04:32,620 --> 00:04:41,699
The caffeine's residual effects can last even longer.

58
00:04:41,699 --> 00:04:46,579
If you want to optimize caffeine's effects on your body, experts suggest abstaining from

59
00:04:46,579 --> 00:04:54,980
caffeine in the afternoon so your cup of coffee the following morning has more impact.

60
00:04:54,980 --> 00:04:57,379
Coffee also requires care when it's drunk.

61
00:04:57,379 --> 00:05:02,500
